IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: ATTACHMENT 1 ATTACHMENT 1TO HOLD TITLE TO PROPERTY, COLLECT INCOME AND REMIT NET INCOME TO THE TEACHERS RETIREMENT SYSTEM OF ILLINOIS, ITS SOLE SHAREHOLDER.
IRS990.MissionDesc: ATTACHMENT 2 ATTACHMENT 2THE CORPORATION IS A 501(C)(25) ORGANIZATION. IT WAS ORGANIZED FORTHE EXCLUSIVE PURPOSE OF HOLDING TITLE TO REAL PROPERTY, COLLECTINGINCOME FROM SUCH PROPERTY, AND REMITTING THE ENTIRE AMOUNT OF INCOMEFROM SUCH PROPERTY (LESS EXPENSES) TO THE SHAREHOLDER OF THISCORPORATION. THE SOLE SHAREHOLDER OF THIS CORPORATION IS THE TEACHERSRETIREMENT SYSTEM OF THE STATE OF ILLINOIS, WHICH IS A TAX-EXEMPTPENSION FUND THAT MEETS THE REQUIREMENTS OF SECTION 401(A) OF THEINTERNAL REVENUE CODE AS AMENDED, WHICH TRUSTS ARE EXEMPT FROMTAXATION UNDER SECTION 501(A) OF THE CODE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: LINE 3: MANAGEMENT AND CONTROL OF ALL DUTIES FOR OPERATIONS ARE DELEGATED TO HEITMAN CAPITAL MANAGEMENT LLC. LINE 6: THE SOLE SHAREHOLDER OF THE ORGANIZATION IS THE TEACHERS RETIREMENT SYSTEM OF ILLINOIS. LINE 7B: THE SOLE SHAREHOLDER REVIEWS AND APPROVES THE ACQUISITIONS, DISPOSITIONS AND REFINANCING OF THE INVESTMENTS. LINE 11B: AN OFFICER REVIEWS A DRAFT OF THE TAX RETURN PROVIDED BY THE TAX RETURN PREPARER. AN OFFICER THEN APPROVES THE DRAFT OR PROVIDES CHANGES AND CORRECTIONS TO THE PREPARER. UPON APPROVAL, A FINAL COPY IS ISSUED TO THE TAXPAYER FOR FILING. A COPY OF THE RETURN IS KEPT ON FILE AND IS AVAILABLE FOR REVIEW UPON REQUEST. LINE 12C: THE DELEGATED MANAGEMENT COMPANY, HEITMAN CAPITAL MANAGEMENT LLC HAS A WRITTEN CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY. THE POTENTIAL FOR CONFLICTS IS MINIMIZED BY ANNUAL REVIEWS AND QUESTIONNAIRES. THE OFFICERS AND THE GOVERNING BODY, AS WELL AS ALL EMPLOYEES AND CONTRACTORS HEITMAN CAPITAL MANAGEMENT LLC ARE AWARE OF THE POLICY. NO SPECIFIC ENFORCEMENT HAS BEEN NECESSARY. LINE 15B: THE ORGANIZATION HAS NO EMPLOYEES. NEITHER THE OFFICERS NOR THE GOVERNING BODY, RECEIVE COMPENSATION FROM THE ORGANIZATION. THESE PERSONS ARE COMPENSATED AND REVIEWED BY THE MANAGEMENT COMPANY, HEITMAN CAPITAL MANAGEMENT LLC. LINE 19: UPON REQUEST, THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS TAX RETURNS, FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AVAILABLE FOR PUBLIC INSPECTION BY FURNISHING A COPY TO THE REQUESTING PERSON.
